Ubuntu users -
--------------

	1. Get liballegro4.2-dev

		$ sudo apt-get install liballegro4.2-dev

	2. Compile nincompoop

		$ g++ main.cpp -o nincompoop -lalleg-4.2.2

	3. Run nincompoop to test

		$ ./nincompoop


Non Ubuntu users / if liballegro4.2 is not in your repository -
---------------------------------------------------------------

	1. Get allegro 4.2.x source from svn

		http://wiki.allegro.cc/index.php?title=Allegro_development#4.2.x

	2. Follow instructions to build liballegro, install

	3. Compile nincompoop

		$ g++ main.cpp -o nincompoop -lalleg-4.2.2

	4. Have fun

		$ ./nincompoop


